   <refnamediv>
       <refname>fuslist</refname>
               <refpurpose>merge vectors of a list </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[vecout]=fuslist(listin)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
<listitem><para>*  <term> listin </term> =    the list of vectors to fusion </para></listitem>
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
<listitem><para>*  <term> vecout</term>  =    the fusion </para></listitem>
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Makes the fusion between the vectors of a list. Each component of the list must be a (n,1) vector  

        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
vec1=1:2:7;
vec2=0:2:8
numx3=fuslist(list(vec1,vec2)) 
 

               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
